─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
FLAWS FOUND AND RESOLVED
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Seven flaws were identified in the initial execution layer implementation
against the execution engine plan. All were resolved.

FLAW 1 — CRITICAL — Race condition on create (FIXED)
  Problem:  unitOfMeasureNameExists + createUnitOfMeasureRecord were two
            un-transacted round-trips. Two concurrent creates with the same
            name could both pass the uniqueness check before either insert
            completed. P2002 catch was a band-aid, not a boundary.
  Fix:      createUnitOfMeasureUseCase wrapped in withDatabaseTransaction.
            Both the check and the write execute inside the same transaction.
  File:     packages/execution/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/create-unit-of-measure.ts

FLAW 2 — CRITICAL — Race condition on update + un-transacted read-back (FIXED)
  Problem:  unitOfMeasureNameExists + updateUnitOfMeasureRecord were two
            un-transacted round-trips (same race condition as Flaw 1).
            Additionally, getUnitOfMeasureById was called after the write
            in a separate un-transacted trip. A concurrent mutation between
            write and read-back would return a snapshot that did not reflect
            the committed write — violating the authoritative snapshot model.
  Fix:      updateUnitOfMeasureUseCase wrapped in withDatabaseTransaction.
            The uniqueness check, write, and read-back all execute inside
            the same transaction. The returned snapshot is guaranteed to
            reflect exactly the write that was committed.
  File:     packages/execution/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/update-unit-of-measure.ts

FLAW 3 — MEDIUM — Prisma _count shape leaking into Application layer (FIXED)
  Problem:  deleteUnitOfMeasureUseCase directly accessed deleteState._count.*
            fields (sendUnitCategories, stockUnitCategories, etc.) to compute
            categoryLinks and serviceLinks. The classification of which schema
            relations constitute a "category link" vs a "service link" is a
            business rule — it was executing in Application on a raw Prisma struct.
  Fix:      getUnitOfMeasureDeleteState in the DB layer now returns
            UnitOfMeasureDeleteStateResult = { categoryLinks: number, serviceLinks: number }
            directly. The aggregation of _count fields happens inside the DB
            function, which owns the schema knowledge. Application receives the
            clean semantic shape and hands it straight to isUnitOfMeasureDeleteBlocked
            from @builders/domain. No _count access anywhere outside the db layer.
  Files:    packages/db/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/read-repository.ts
            packages/execution/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/delete-unit-of-measure.ts

FLAW 4 — MEDIUM — normalizeNameForUniqueness duplicated across both use cases (FIXED)
  Problem:  An identical private function was defined independently inside
            create-unit-of-measure.ts and update-unit-of-measure.ts. This is
            a domain rule (what "normalized for uniqueness" means for a UOM name)
            living outside the domain package, duplicated.
  Fix:      Promoted to packages/domain/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/name-rules.ts
            as normalizeUnitOfMeasureNameForUniqueness. Exported from
            @builders/domain index. Both use cases now import from @builders/domain.
            The features domain file (unit-of-measure-rules.ts) re-exports it
            from @builders/domain instead of defining it locally.
  Files:    packages/domain/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/name-rules.ts (NEW)
            packages/domain/src/index.ts
            packages/execution/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/create-unit-of-measure.ts
            packages/execution/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/update-unit-of-measure.ts
            apps/web/features/flooring/unit-of-measures/domain/unit-of-measure-rules.ts

FLAW 5 — LOW — Missing type guard on UnitOfMeasureExecutionError (FIXED)
  Problem:  The allocation reference implementation exports
            isWorkOrderAllocationExecutionError as a type guard. The UOM
            error class had no equivalent. Callers needing to conditionally
            handle UOM errors had no safe guard to use.
  Fix:      isUnitOfMeasureExecutionError added to errors.ts.
  File:     packages/execution/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/errors.ts

FLAW 6 — LOW — Missing payload field on UnitOfMeasureExecutionError (FIXED)
  Problem:  The allocation error class carries readonly payload?: Record<string, unknown>
            for structured error metadata. UOM omitted it, diverging from the
            reference pattern and requiring a breaking change if payload is ever needed.
  Fix:      payload field added to UnitOfMeasureExecutionError constructor and class body.
  File:     packages/execution/src/flooring/unit-of-measures/errors.ts

FLAW 7 — LOW — Split import blocks from same package (FIXED)
  Problem:  create-unit-of-measure.ts and update-unit-of-measure.ts each had
            two separate import statements from @builders/db (one for Prisma,
            one for repository functions).
  Fix:      Consolidated into a single import block per package in both files.
